pageContext.claim: “I wish they could have told us earlier about it because we could have come up with a solution. Tony Fauci and all of the people -- the talent that we have -- would have loved to have had three or four months of additional time, if you knew what this was going to be happening....If we had a two- or three-month difference in time, it would have been much better.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump's timeline of "three to four months" additional time of warning from China makes no sense. The first possible case was identified in China on Dec. 1. The head of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention learned of a possible new coronavirus from his Chinese counterpart on Jan. 3, days before Chinese researchers {publicly said} they had identified a new virus. The first death in China was recorded on Jan. 11.
